Source:  Kauri-Gum
Author:  PATTERSON
Vol / Page:  6
Edition:
Quote:  in former times, even in winter, `hooking' has been practised in the swamps.....The necessary tools were a long spear and a long hook - a long iron rod with a curved end. The gum.....found by the spear.....[was] worked up through the slime with the hook.
